revision.text:
'''Aelianus''' was together with Amandus the leader of an insurrection of Gallic peasants, called [[Bagaudae]], in the reign of [[Diocletian]].  It was put down by the [[Maximian|Caesar Maximianus Herculius]] in 285.<ref>Eutrop., ix. 13</ref><ref>Aurel. Vict., ''de Caes'' 89</ref><ref>{{Citation  | last = Smith  | first = William  | author-link = William Smith (lexicographer)  | contribution = Aelianus  | editor-last = Smith  | editor-first = William  | title = [[Dictionary of Greek and Roman Biography and Mythology]]  | volume = 1  | pages = 28  | place = Boston  | year = 1867  | contribution-url = http://www.ancientlibrary.com/smith-bio/0037.html }}</ref>

