'''Shinya Tasaki''' ([[Japanese name]]: 田崎真也 born: 21 March 1958) is a [[Japanese people|Japanese]] [[sommelier]] who was  named best sommelier in the world in 1995 by the [[Association de la Sommellerie Internationale]].<ref>[http://www.sommellerie-internationale.com/ sommellerie-internationale.com]</ref>
Tasaki is the only Asian national ever to win the title of the Best Sommelier of the World, and he was awarded the [[Medals of Honor (Japan)|Yellow Ribbon Medal of Honor]] by the [[Emperor of Japan]].<ref>[http://www.decanter.com/dawa/the-dawa-judges/dawa-judge-shinya-tasaki-17411/ Decanter Asia Wine Awards vice-chair: Shinya Tasaki] ''[[Decanter (magazine)|Decanter]]'' September 19, 2017</ref>

